@Coleen17 on a clean machine with SDK 9.0.300 + latest build of Aspire 9.3.0, I'm unable to reproduce this issue anymore. Can you try again? You can close this issue if it does not reproduce anymore.

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6eff010f-3646-4436-a495-fad63483e267)

@v-elenafeng

@karolz-ms I've been looking at how we might be able to get logs from the DCP reconcilers when they are relevant to specific resources and make them show up in the dashboard. For example, let's say the service reconciler is failing because a port is already in use.

We pipe the DCP logs to the apphost logs, but its tricky to correctly parse out which message might be relevant for a specific resource.

I'm looking at the output text in the logs and there is a enough inconsistency there between the various reconcilers that makes me think I could get this wrong if I started trying to crack open the JSON payload on the string :)

@copilot update this code https://github.com/dotnet/aspire/blob/ef7b5b268776076185357a654a503211abff0195/src/Aspire.Hosting/Publishing/PublishingActivityReporter.cs#L268

Any unsupported interactions should fail instead instead of return.

See https://github.com/dotnet/aspire/blob/ef7b5b268776076185357a654a503211abff0195/src/Aspire.Hosting/Publishing/PublishingActivityReporter.cs#L275-L284 for an example on how failures should look.
